raw_data.title: Cyber Security Health Engineer 3
raw_data.description: Design, Develop and deploy security tools, systems, and health IT architectures to protect against cyber threats. Develop and enforce security policies and procedures. Maintain security best practices, access controls, and other health IT security measures. Integrate security into the software development lifecycle (SDLC) for health IT. Be up to date on the latest threats and vulnerabilities and propose health solutions to mitigate them. Investigate and resolve security incidents and breaches. Direct use of security tools and technologies to detect and respond to potential attacks. Respond to security incidents. Mentor and train junior engineers. Ensure compliance with relevant regulations and standards. Implementing and maintaining security controls to meet legal and health industry requirements.
